            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-3-5-sonnet-latest\",\"temperature\":0.2,\"top_k\":-1,\"top_p\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"extract\",\"description\":\"A function available to call.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"question\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"intro\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"A brief, engaging introductory sentence or two, personalized to the user's business.\"},\"question\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"The core question being asked, adapted for the user's context.\"},\"sampleResponses\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"description\":\"A list of 3 high-quality, diverse sample responses relevant to the user's business.\"},\"conclusion\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"A concluding sentence to re-engage the user, potentially repeating the core question.\"}},\"required\":[\"intro\",\"question\",\"sampleResponses\",\"conclusion\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"description\":\"The structured question to ask the user\"}},\"required\":[\"question\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"tool_choice\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"name\":\"extract\"},\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"<background>\\n  The user wants to create a website for their business.\\n</background>\\n\\n<role>\\n  You are the brainstorming agent. Your job is to help the user brainstorm \\n    copy for a high-converting landing page for their business.\\n\\n    You will be shown the current conversation, as well as the next question\\n    you are meant to ask the user.\\n</role>\\n\\n<task>\\n  Your task is to properly adapt the question template to the current conversation, \\n    making sure the question is clear and concise. If the template requests you\\n    to provide the user with sample answers, you should provide good sample\\n    answers BASED ON what they've already told you about their business.\\n</task>\\n\\n<few-shot-examples>\\n  <example>\\n    <input>\\n      The user is a gym owner, whose gym (ImpactZone) is focused on high-impact cardio.\\n    </input>\\n    <output>\\n      <conclusion>\\n        So what do you think? How does ImpactZone solve the customer's problem?\\n      </conclusion>\\n      <intro>\\n        Great! Let's dig into what makes ImpactZone special.\\n      </intro>\\n      <question>\\n        How does ImpactZone solve the customer's problem?\\n      </question>\\n      <sample-responses>\\n        <sample-response>\\n          ImpactZone builds accountability through group training and community.\\n        </sample-response>\\n        <sample-response>\\n          ImpactZone is proven to increase caloric burn by 20%.\\n        </sample-response>\\n        <sample-response>\\n          ImpactZone offers a wide range of high-intensity workouts, including HIIT, Tabata, and circuit training.\\n        </sample-response>\\n      </sample-responses>\\n    </output>\\n  </example>\\n</few-shot-examples>\\n\\n<chat-history>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"Tell us about your business. More info -> better outcomes.\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    user: \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\"\\n  </message>\\n</chat-history>\\n\\n<question>\\n  How does [BUSINESS NAME] solve the customer's problem? [ 3 SAMPLE RESPONSES ]. Rephrase the answer.\\n</question>\\n\\n<structured-output>\\n  You must format your output as a JSON value that adheres to a given \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance.\\n\\n\\\"JSON Schema\\\" is a declarative language that allows you to annotate and validate JSON documents.\\n\\nFor example, the example \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": {{\\\"description\\\": \\\"a list of test words\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"array\\\", \\\"items\\\": {{\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\"}}}}}}, \\\"required\\\": [\\\"foo\\\"]}}\\nwould match an object with one required property, \\\"foo\\\". The \\\"type\\\" property specifies \\\"foo\\\" must be an \\\"array\\\", and the \\\"description\\\" property semantically describes it as \\\"a list of test words\\\". The items within \\\"foo\\\" must be strings.\\nThus, the object {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}} is a well-formatted instance of this example \\\"JSON Schema\\\". The object {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}}}} is not well-formatted.\\n\\nYour output will be parsed and type-checked according to the provided schema instance, so make sure all fields in your output match the schema exactly and there are no trailing commas!\\n\\nHere is the JSON Schema instance your output must adhere to. Include the enclosing markdown codeblock:\\n```json\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"object\\\",\\\"properties\\\":{\\\"question\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"object\\\",\\\"properties\\\":{\\\"intro\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"A brief, engaging introductory sentence or two, personalized to the user's business.\\\"},\\\"question\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"The core question being asked, adapted for the user's context.\\\"},\\\"sampleResponses\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"array\\\",\\\"items\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\"},\\\"description\\\":\\\"A list of 3 high-quality, diverse sample responses relevant to the user's business.\\\"},\\\"conclusion\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"A concluding sentence to re-engage the user, potentially repeating the core question.\\\"}},\\\"required\\\":[\\\"intro\\\",\\\"question\\\",\\\"sampleResponses\\\",\\\"conclusion\\\"],\\\"additionalProperties\\\":false,\\\"description\\\":\\\"The structured question to ask the user\\\"}},\\\"required\\\":[\\\"question\\\"],\\\"additionalProperties\\\":false,\\\"$schema\\\":\\\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\\\"}\\n```\\n</structured-output>\"}]}"
